This rifle was built by FN in the 90s for the West Virginia State Police. A total of three were made and this happens to be one of them. title: For Sale:  Colt Single Action
postcontent: very nice and all matching 1st Generation Colt Single Action Army pistol chambered in 45 Colt that left the factory on July 6th 1875. It was shipped to J.P. Moores & Sons New York City NY in a shipment of 45 guns. The Colt factory letter accompanies this fine pistol. This is a rare civilian model that was blued with a case colored frame and 1 piece walnut grips. The pistol has all matching numbers with its original grips. The mechanics are excellent with no issues. The indexing, timing and lockup are as new and solid as a vault. The barrel address is of the 1st style Italicized lettering and all frame markings are crisp and legible with no hint of any tampering at all. The bore is excellent with strong lands and grooves and shiny from muzzle to chamber. The cylinder walls are excellent also with shiny finish original blue remaining. This fine Peacemaker locks up tight as a vault with all 4 audible clicks. The barrel and cylinder blue has worn or flaked off but there still remains the original charcoal blueing on the trigger guard and front and back straps. You can see the original bright blueing on the flats. There are small remains of faded case colors on the frame. All metal edges are sharp and flush as they were when the gun left the factory. The grips could have been refinished long ago but fit tight with no gaps and no cracks or repairs of any kind. There is no play in the action anywhere and the original mainspring is as strong as the day it was made. The hammer retains its sharp factory bordered checkering which is indicative of little use. A beautiful and rare Colt SAA pistol for the advanced Colt collector and one that is missing in most advanced collections. Not many Colt SAA's of this period remain today and when usually seen are plain no finish guns with much heavy wear, chopped barrels and replaced or missing parts. Original Colt Civilian SAA's from 1874, 1875 and 1876 are real prizes for the advanced collector.

I am selling my AR-15 pistol upper.  It has a 10" barrel and is threaded 1/2-28 standard for flash hider, etc.  It comes with the f-marked A2 front sight, A2 flash hider, and standard M4 style waffle foreend grip.  The bayonet lug is cut off so the flash hider could be tucked closer to the front sight. The barrel itself is a palmetto state armory (PSA) M4 profile, 1-7 twist, non-chrome lined. The upper reciever is a PSA forged, all the other small parts are PSA as well. 

This is for the Upper Barreled assembly only, so it does not come with the pistol lower.  It does not come with a bolt carrier group or charging handle. It does not come with the rear flip up sight that is shown in the pic, and it will have a standard M4 waffle style foregrip and not the pictured magpul foregrip. 

This upper shoots fine, it runs 100% with good 5.56 ammo (federal XM193, etc). I was using a standard M4 buffer and spring, and standard FA BCG. 

This upper is only legal on an AR pistol lower, unless you have an NFA lower and if you have that then you know the rules.  It is your responsibility to know the laws regarding the differences between AR rifle lowers and legal AR pistols. 

I will only sell this to a CCW holder. Cash only sale.
